      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">32.112-2</ph> Subcontractor requests
for information.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d2030e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2055e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> In accordance with section 806(a)(1) of Public Law 102-190, as amended by sections 2091 and 8105 of Public Law 103-355 <ph rev="FAC 2023-01 December 30, 2022"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022-005?>(<xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/uscode/10/4601"
                           format="html"
                           scope="external">10 U.S.C. 4601 note</xref> prec.),<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 32.112-2 by removing from paragraph (a) introductory text “ 10 U.S.C. 2302 note” and adding “10 U.S.C. 4601 note prec.” in its place.?></ph> upon the request of a subcontractor or supplier under a Federal contract other than for a commercial product or commercial service, the contracting officer shall promptly advise the subcontractor or supplier as to— </p>
               <ol id="d2030e26" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2055e19">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Whether the prime contractor has
submitted requests for progress payments or other payments to the
Federal Government under the contract; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2055e24">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Whether
final payment under the contract has been made by the Federal Government
to the prime contractor.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2055e29">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> In accordance
with <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">5 U.S.C.552(b)(1)</xref>,
this subsection does not apply to matters that are-</p>
               <ol id="d2030e59" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2055e38">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Specifically
authorized under criteria established by an Executive order to be
kept classified in the interest of national defense or foreign policy;
and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2055e43">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Properly
classified pursuant to such Executive order.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
